  "retryPrompt": "Research topic: \"I am searching for a new role and want to explore job boards to see if there is a role that fits.\"\n\nBackground context:\nYou are a job search agent helping Matt Stanton find his next role. Here is his candidate profile and search criteria to use when evaluating opportunities:BackgroundMatt is a Senior Product Manager with 10+ years of experience building and launching hardware and software products in industrial and field-deployed environments. He has deep experience in computer vision, AI/ML product development, robotics, NPI, and industrial analytics. He has been a founding or first PM at multiple companies and does his best work in early, ambiguous environments where product decisions shape company direction. He holds two degrees in Mechanical Engineering from Carnegie Mellon and is a Forbes 30 Under 30 honoree.Recent experience anchorsAMP Robotics: Owned roadmap for AI-enabled robotic sorting and computer vision systems. Scaled CV deployments from 30 to 400+ worldwide. Led NPI programs, worked directly with ML teams on segmentation, model evaluation, and ground truth workflows.VALIS: First product hire at a seed-stage industrial AI startup. Took a hardware-enabled analytics platform from 0 to 1. Landed 2 of the top 5 customers in the market, both expanded. Stood up product, customer success, and operations from scratch.SolePower: Co-founded a consumer hardware company, raised $1M+, secured DoD contracts and SBIR grants.What he is looking forTitles: Senior PM, Principal PM, Head of Product, Forward Deployed Engineer, AI Solutions Lead, or equivalentStage: Series A/B startups preferred; late stage companies considered if the role has a clear 0-to-1 mandate and startup-like energyIndustries: Robotics and automation, industrial and manufacturing, computer vision, field services, construction, waste and recycling, climate and cleantech, agentic and voice AIRole type: First or founding PM with ownership of product direction, roadmap, and direct customer engagement; path to Head of Product preferredOpen to: Consulting, fractional, and 1099 arrangementsHard requirementsFully remote, up to 25% travelBase salary of $175K or aboveRole posted within the last 14 daysIf salary or posting date cannot be confirmed, flag the role but still surface it if the fit is strongNot a fitPure software PM roles with no physical systems or hardware contextLarge enterprise roles without a 0-to-1 componentRoles requiring fixed office presenceRoles outside the USEvaluation criteriaWhen evaluating a role score it out of 10 based on: alignment with target industries, 0-to-1 mandate, remote status, compensation, company stage, and how well the technical requirements match Matt's background in CV, AI, robotics, and industrial systems. Flag any gaps honestly.\n\nIMPORTANT: A previous search on this topic returned insufficient results (only 0 findings could be verified). This is a follow-up search to fill the gaps.\n\nDate range: focus on content published between March 28, 2026 and April 4, 2026 (last 7 days).\nPlease search for 5 additional findings. Focus specifically on:\n- Concrete, recent data points (numbers, percentages, named companies or people)\n- Pages that are publicly accessible (avoid paywalled or login-required content)\n- Each finding MUST have a direct, full source URL in [Source Name](URL) format\nPrioritize content from these sources: , i, bu, wel.\nFocus especially on these areas: .\n\n\nAdditional context from uploaded document:\nPK\u0003\u0004\u0014\u0000\b\b\b\u0000�}\\\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0012\u0000\u0000\u0000word/numbering.xml՗]n\u001a1\u0010�O�;��\u001e���&(K\u0014%J�*�*%=��\u001a��\u001f+�\u0017B/��ޯ'�x�\b�T\u000by)/�����3x=���E�h!\u001cHk\u0012���$\u0012��T�YB~<ߟ\\�\b<3)Sֈ��\u0004�����\u0014z\"\u001c�E�00�<!����R���\fz6\u0017\u0006�S�4���fT37/�\u0013nuμ�H%��\u000e�xHj�MH�̨F�hɝ\u0005;�!ed�S�E�4\u0019�˾Uʝ�\u0016Ɨ;R'\u0014j�\u00062�CCӇ�Й5�ſ�X